aa(lp211
VFinally, the more approachable, the more inclusive,
p212
aVand the more diverse we make the world of technology,
p213
aVthe more colorful and better the world will look like.
p214
aVSo, imagine with me, for a moment,
p215
aVa world where the stories we tell
p216
aVabout how things get made don't only include
p217
aVthe twentysomething-year-old Silicon Valley boys,
p218
aVbut also Kenyan schoolgirls and Norwegian librarians.
p219
aVImagine a world where the little Ada Lovelaces of tomorrow,
p220
aVwho live in a permanent reality of 1s and 0s,
p221
aVthey grow up to be very optimistic and brave about technology.
p222
aVThey embrace the powers and the opportunities
p223
aVand the limitations of the world.
p224
aVA world of technology that is wonderful, whimsical
p225
aVand a tiny bit weird.
